Kuznetsova, Zvonareva win Australian Open doubles
2012-01-27 10:35:48 GMT
MELBOURNE, Jan. 27 (Xinhua) -- Russian veterans Svetlana Kuznetsova and Vera Zvonareva won the 2012 Australian Open women's doubles title here on Friday after beating Italian duo of Sara Errani and Roberta Vinci 5-7, 6-4, 6-3.The unseed Russians captured the decisive break in the second game of the third set and survived five break points before earning the victory over the 11th-seeded Italian pair.It is their first Grand Slam title as doubles partners since last year's French Open, though each had won major doubles titles separately.Kuznetsova won the 2005 Australian Open with Australian Alicia Molik, while Zvonareva won the 2006 U.S. Open with Nathalie Dechy of French.Kuznetsova and Zvonareva are both known primarily for their singles accomplishments. Both the Russians have been as high as No.2 in the world individually, with Kuznetsova having French and U.S. Open singles trophies.
